<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> A's Name Heredia To Start Opener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Gil Heredia was picked today to start the Oakland  
Athletic's season opener Monday night against five-time Cy Young 
Award winner Roger Clemens and the New York Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
	Heredia, who began the spring as the team's No. 4 starter,  
replaces Kenny Rogers, who said he wasn't in shape yet. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was the best fit for us going into the season,'' manager  
Art Howe said. ``He's going to give us a good outing. He's capable 
of beating anybody.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Heredia was chosen over Tom Candiotti, who would have pitched on  
three days' rest, and Jimmy Haynes, scheduled to pitch Friday 
against the San Francisco Giants. 
</P>
<P>
	``If I look shaken up or confused, it's because it's obviously a  
surprise,'' Heredia said. ``It's an honor, a prestige thing.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Heredia was signed to a minor league contract by the A's in 1998  
and spent most of the season at Triple-A Edmonton. He was recalled 
on Aug. 22 and went 3-3 with an ERA of 2.74. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's been around long enough to handle the situation,'' Howe  
said. ``When we told him, he was all pumped up.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Heredia has pitched for the Giants, Montreal Expos and Texas  
Rangers in a major league career that began in 1991. He has a 22-24 
career record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
