<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 14-Day Bills Go at 4.85 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Treasury Department sold 14-day cash  
management bills on Wednesday at a discount rate of 4.85 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The discount rate understates the actual return to investors --  
4.95 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,981.10. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of $26 billion in bills were sold out of bids totaling  
$42.8 billion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
