<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cloude To Start Season in Minors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PEORIA, Ariz. (AP) -- Ken Cloude, who came to spring training as  
the Seattle Mariners' No. 3 starter, will start the season in the 
minors. 
</P>
<P>
	The 24-year-old right-hander was optioned today to Triple-A  
Tacoma of the Pacific Coast League along with right-hander Rafael 
Carmona and left-hander Greg McCarthy. 
</P>
<P>
	Seattle reassigned catcher Raul Chavez to its minor league camp.  
Chavez also is expected to start the season in Tacoma. 
</P>
<P>
	Cloude, a sixth-round pick in the 1993 amateur draft, spent most  
of last season with the Mariners, going 8-10 with a 6.37 ERA in 30 
starts and 155 1-3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	He pitched poorly this spring, going 0-3 with a 12.67 ERA in  
five games -- and four starts -- and 16 1-3 innings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
