<HEADLINE> Tour Bus Crash Injures 40 in Calif. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NIPTON, Calif. (AP) -- A tour bus loaded with children collided  
with a truck carrying strawberries on a remote stretch of 
Interstate 15 late Tuesday, injuring 40 people, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	The crash happened at about 10 p.m. in the northbound lanes of  
the highway that connects Southern California with Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
	It was not clear what caused the crash, but the bus ended up in  
a ditch, said Dennis West of the San Bernardino County Fire 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is out there in the middle of nowhere,'' he said. ``We've  
had patrol cars on the road for an hour who still haven't gotten to 
the scene because it's so far.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The bus driver was reported to be in critical condition, six  
people suffered moderate injuries and the 33 children aboard had 
minor injuries, West said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Its mostly just bumps, bruises, scrapes and scratches,'' he  
said of the children's injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	The children, who were returning to the Henderson, Nev., area,  
were being taken to a Las Vegas hospital for observation, West 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Nipton is 65 miles south of Las Vegas near the California-Nevada  
line. 
</P>
