<HEADLINE> Cops Kill Suspect in Texas Murders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- A man suspected in the shooting deaths  
of his girlfriend and three other Abilene women was killed 
Wednesday in a gun battle with police. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers pulled over a white car on a Fort Worth highway about 9  
p.m. and someone in the car pulled a gun, police told Abilene TV 
station KTXS. Shots were exchanged, killing 19-year-old Arthur 
Goodman. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodman had been sought as a suspect in the Monday night  
shootings of his girlfriend, Sandy Witt, 20, Penny Estrada, 21, 
Naomi Martinez, 23, and Erica Arispe, 21. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said Goodman may have killed Ms. Witt in her apartment  
because she would not provide him with a false alibi in connection 
with an undisclosed crime he was suspected in. 
</P>
<P>
	The other victims were killed because they happened to be at the  
apartment, police said. A fifth victim, an apartment maintenance 
man, was wounded in the attack. 
</P>
<P>
	Goodman was charged Tuesday with capital murder. Police also  
wanted to question his 16-year-old brother, who might have been 
with him when the shooting happened, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers also suspect Goodman in the Sunday night shooting of a  
16-year-old boy who survived. 
</P>
