<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Stocks End Down / Japanese Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- The Tokyo Stock Exchange's main index slipped in  
volatile trading today, the last day of Japan's fiscal year. The 
dollar was lower against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 119.98 yen at late afternoon, down 0.02 yen  
from late Tuesday in Tokyo and also lower than its level of 120.36 
yen in New York overnight. 
</P>
<P>
	The 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average shed 22.53 points, or 0.14  
percent, closing the day at 15,836.59. On Tuesday, the index lost 
149.72 points, or 0.94 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Share prices opened the session slightly higher following  
weakness in Nikkei futures and an overnight fall on Wall Street. 
</P>
<P>
	But the Nikkei average soon moved into negative territory on  
profit-taking following the market's recent strong gains, losing as 
much as 207 points before reducing some of its losses. 
</P>
<P>
	The average has climbed about 15 percent this year.  
</P>
<P>
	``U.S. pension funds were buying for window dressing purposes  
throughout the day,'' said Dhia Amir, senior institutional sales 
trader at Nomura Securities. 
</P>
<P>
	Traders said, however, that buying was outpaced by domestic  
profit taking and selling by investors with bonds linked to the 
stock market. 
</P>
<P>
	Trading was moderate, with about 480 million shares changing  
hands on the exchange's first section, compared with Tuesday's 
turnover of 464 million shares. Advances outnumbered retreaters 716 
to 460, with 137 issues unchanged. 
</P>
<P>
	The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the  
first section was down 2.02 points, or 0.16 percent, to 1,267.22. 
The TOPIX had risen 0.57 points, or 0.04 percent, the previous day. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, the dollar moved as high as 120.98 yen earlier today  
on strong buying from Japanese financial institutions. 
</P>
<P>
	But the greenback later shed its early gains on selling by  
Japanese exporters and overseas players, including U.S. funds, 
traders said. 
</P>
<P>
	Trading was relatively range bound in Tokyo today, the last day  
of Japan's fiscal year. Japan's new fiscal year begins on April 1. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar ranged between 119.90 yen and 120.98 yen in today's  
trading. 
</P>
<P>
	In other currencies, the euro was traded at 128.59 yen, lower  
from 128.78 yen late Tuesday in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield on the benchmark No. 211 10-year Japanese government  
bond rose to 1.745 percent from Tuesday's finish of 1.740 percent, 
driving its price down to 100.47 yen from 100.51 yen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
