<HEADLINE> Fleeting Image Wins Irish O'Brien </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Fleeting Image, a 6-year-old who had been  
winless since the first running of the Irish O'Brien Stakes last 
year, won the race again Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by David Flores and carrying 116 pounds, Fleeting Image  
won in 1:15 2-5, defeating favored Supercilious by 1 1/4 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
	Fleeting Image, who had raced seven times between her Irish  
O'Brien victories, paid $13.40, $5.40 and $4.20. The win was the 
sixth in 20 lifetime starts and was worth $64,380. 
</P>
<P>
	Supercilious crossed the finish line a nose in front of Pert  
Laura and returned $3.20 and $2.60. 
</P>
<P>
	Pert Laura, a 28-1 longshot, paid $6.60 to show.  
</P>
</TEXT>
