<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Emergency Trunk Releases for Fords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Ford Motor Co. said it will be the first major  
car maker to install an emergency trunk release as a standard 
feature on a wide range of cars. 
</P>
<P>
	All Ford, Lincoln and Mercury cars sold in the United States and  
Canada will include this feature, Ken Kohrs, a Ford vice president, 
said at the New York Auto Show on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The system features a cable-operated release inside the trunk. A  
T-shaped handle will be made of phosphorescent material so it glows 
in the dark, Ford said in disclosing details of a feature already 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
	Nineteen children have died in the past decade after  
inadvertently locking themselves inside trunks, according to the 
National Highway Traffic Safety Administration. Last summer, the 
victims included 11 children ages 2 to 6 -- five in Utah, two in 
Greensboro, Pa., and four in Gallup, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
	General Motors Corp. announced last December that it would have  
trunk release handles available for installation as optional 
equipment by this spring. 


</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
