<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *PepsiCo Inc. fell 11/16 to 39 3/16.  
</P>
<P>
 *Pepsi Bottling Group, closed at 21 11/16, down from an original 
price of 23. 
</P>
<P>
	PepsiCo spun off the Bottling Group in an initial public  
offering of 100 million shares priced at $23 each. The price was at 
the low end of the estimated range of $23 to $26, an indication 
that pre-pricing demand was less than the company had anticipated. 

</P>
<P>
 *Ziff-Davis Inc. fell 7 1/2 to 21 1/2.  
</P>
<P>
 *ZDnet, closed at 36, up from an original price of 19. 
</P>
<P>
	Ziff-Davis, the publishing and marketing company, issued  
``tracking stock'' for its ZDNet Internet unit priced at $19 each. 
Tracking stock involves shares that trade separately to follow the 
performance of part of a company, but do not pay separate 
dividends. 

</P>
<P>
 *KCS Energy fell 7/16 to 1 7/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	The natural gas and crude oil company widened its fourth-quarter  
loss to $8.68 a share from $3.63 a year ago and said the remainder 
of 1999 and 2000 would be challenging. The company hired a 
financial adviser to review strategic alternatives and its chief 
financial officer resigned. 

</P>
<P>
 *LSI Logic rose 3 11/16 to 31 3/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	Morgan Stanley upgraded the integrated circuit maker's stock to  
``strong buy'' from ``neutral.'' 

</P>
<P>
 *Cendant Corp. rose 5/8 to 15 15/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company said Tuesday it will increase its share repurchase  
program by $200 million, to $1.6 billion. 

</P>
<P>
 *Ingram Micro Inc. rose 3 13/16 to 22 13/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The California-based computer distributor laid off 235 employees  
at its Orange County headquarters as part of a major retrenchment. 
The company, which serves customers in North and South America, 
Europe and Asia, announced March 11 that it would eliminate 1,400 
jobs throughout the company in the face of tougher price 
competition and slack demand. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *PeopleSoft Inc. fell 15/16 to 14 5/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	Joining other makers of business software, the company warned  
first-quarter revenue and operating margin will come in below 
expectations, citing a slowdown in software license sales due to 
uncertain market conditions. 

</P>
<P>
 *Etec Systems Inc. fell 13 11/16 to 29 7/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The semiconductor equipment gear maker said third-quarter  
earnings would probably be about 10 cents a share, far below 
analysts' expectations of 26 cents and last year's 47 cents. The 
company citied a slowdown in orders. 

</P>
<P>
 *E.Spire Communications Inc. rose 3/4 to 13 3/4.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company and BankAtlantic Bancorp Inc. formed a joint venture  
to promote Internet services throughout Florida. 

</P>
<P>
 *Tech Data rose 4 1/16 to 22 15/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The Clearwater, Fla., computer distributor reported late Tuesday  
its fourth-quarter net earnings were 64 cents a diluted share, 
topping analysts' estimate by 2 cents and up from 53 cents a year 
ago. On Wednesday, Morgan Stanley upgraded the rating on the stock 
to ``outperform'' from ``neutral.'' 


</P>
</TEXT>
