<HEADLINE> Town Mulls Statue of Shirley Jones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SMITHTON, Pa. (AP) -- They had trouble in River City when Shirley  
Jones starred in ``The Music Man.'' Now the trouble's in her 
hometown. 
</P>
<P>
	Marty Ingels, Jones' husband, wants to give her a statue and a  
park for her birthday, but city officials don't want to have to 
maintain them. 
</P>
<P>
	``Our entire city budget is $35,000. I know the car Marty drives  
is worth more than that,'' said Fred Foster, president of the City 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
	Ingels is fed up with the town of 400, about 30 miles from  
Pittsburgh, and may put the statue at Westmoreland County Community 
College 10 miles away. 
</P>
<P>
	``What started out to be a lovely, joyous thing has become  
Vietnam, Hiroshima -- a nightmare for me,'' Ingels said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
