<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European 200m Champion Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BIRMINGHAM, England (AP) -- European 200-meter champion Doug  
Walker was in ``total shock'' after his suspension for a failed 
drug test. 
</P>
<P>
	Walker is barred from competition pending a hearing by UK  
Athletics. The governing body of British track and field said the 
25-year-old Scot had the steroid Nandrolone in his system during an 
out-of-competition test in December. 
</P>
<P>
	He faces a two-year ban, which would eliminate him from the  
world championships in August in Spain. A date for his hearing has 
not been set. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't have any real explanation,'' Walker said. ``I've  
always been careful with everything I've taken. 
</P>
<P>
	UK Athletics spokeswoman Jayne Pearce said an independent drug  
advisory committee ruled there was ``sufficient evidence that a 
doping offense has taken place.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``It's very important to note that it is not a declaration of  
guilt; it is a declaration that there is a case to answer,'' Pearce 
told BBC radio. 
</P>
<P>
	The committee met March 23 and Walker had to wait eight days for  
the decision. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a total shock,'' Walker said. ``And when I found out on  
the train this morning it was like my worst nightmare coming 
true.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Walker's lawyer Nick Bitel said his client has been denied  
access to full lab results in accordance with IOC rules. 
</P>
<P>
	``What we want to know is: What is the evidence?'' he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
