<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Brian Setzer  
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Brian Setzer was born in New York on April 10,  
1959. Raised in Massapequa, N.Y., Setzer never seemed to go with 
the flow. 
</P>
<P>
	When he was 8, he started lessons on the euphonium, a brass  
instrument that resembles a tuba. He played the euphonium for 10 
years, and the influence of horns on his music has been strong ever 
since. Even when he started guitar lessons (also at 8), his teacher 
was a saxophone player. 
</P>
<P>
	As a teen-ager, he would cut class and take the train into New  
York to hang around the jazz clubs. Underage, he would sneak into 
places such as the Village Vanguard and Village Gate. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Musical Influences:* Although Setzer was born after the first  
wave of rock 'n' roll hit in the 1950s, he has always preferred the 
music of that period. 
</P>
<P>
	``When I was going to high school, even though it was the '70s,  
it was still the leftover of the '60s. It was hippie; the flower 
thing,'' Setzer said. ``I never connected with it. I had long hair 
but when I was about 15, I just cut it all off. I wanted to look 
like Eddie Cochran rather than Jim Morrison.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Big break:* Brian Setzer and The Stray Cats spearheaded a  
``rockabilly'' revival in the early 1980s with such stripped-down 
hits as ``Stray Cat Strut'' and ``Rock This Town.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But the idea of a big band percolated in Setzer's head. On the  
tour bus, he would listen to Gene Krupa and Bobby Darin, practice 
jazz chords, and imagine how his songs would sound arranged for a 
big band. 
</P>
<P>
	``On the old 'Tonight Show,' bands would come on but Doc  
Severinsen wouldn't be included,'' he said. ``What a waste! I 
always wanted The Stray Cats on so we could play 'Rock This Town' 
with them.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Brian Setzer Orchestra was born in late 1992. The 17-piece  
orchestra is a rambunctious package of rocking jazz, with Setzer's 
guitar ringing loud and clear over swinging charts. Setzer croons, 
too. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:* ``Musically, a big band is pretty hard to beat. It's so  
rich, so powerful. Another thing is, people are tired of going out 
and looking at three or four guys with guitars. With this, there's 
so much to look at. It's entertaining. People are really intrigued 
by it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Awards:* The Brian Setzer Orchestra captured two pop honors at  
this year's Grammys for ``The Dirty Boogie,'' Setzer's third album 
featuring big-band swing with a rockin' twist. 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays April 4-10:  
</P>
<P>
	April 4: Actor Craig T. Nelson is 53. Actress Christine Lahti is  
49. Musician Craig Adams of The Cult is 37. Actor Robert Downey Jr. 
is 34. Actress Nancy McKeon is 33. Actor Barry Pepper (``Saving 
Private Ryan'') is 29. Musician Magnus Sveningsson of The Cardigans 
is 27. Singer Kelly Price is 26. 
</P>
<P>
	April 5: Actor Gregory Peck is 83. Actor Michael Moriarty is 58.  
Singer Agnetha ``Anna'' Faltskog of Abba is 49. Singer Paula Cole 
is 31. 
</P>
<P>
	April 6: Actor Billy Dee Williams is 62. Singer Michelle  
Phillips is 55. Actor John Ratzenberger is 52. Actress Marilu 
Henner is 47. Actor Paul Rudd (``Object of My Affection'') is 30. 
Actor Jason Hervey (``The Wonder Years'') is 27. Actress Candace 
Cameron is 23. 
</P>
<P>
	April 7: Actor James Garner is 71. Movie director Francis Ford  
Coppola is 60. TV personality David Frost is 60. Singer John Oates 
of Hall and Oates is 50. Singer Janis Ian is 48. Actor Jackie Chan 
is 45. Actor Russell Crowe (``The Quick and the Dead'') is 35. 
Singer Victoria Aadams of Spice Girls is 24. 
</P>
<P>
	April 8: Singer-actor John Schneider is 45. Singer Julian Lennon  
is 36. Rapper Biz Markie is 35. Actress Robin Wright Penn is 33. 
Actress Patricia Arquette is 31. Singer Greg Honeycutt of 
Everything is 29. Actor Taran Noah Smith (``Home Improvement'') is 
15. 
</P>
<P>
	April 9: Actress Michael Learned is 60. Actor Dennis Quaid is  
45. Humorist Jimmy Tingle (``60 Minutes II'') is 44. Singer Kevin 
Martin of Candlebox is 30. Actress Keshia Knight Pulliam (``The 
Cosby Show'') is 20. 
</P>
<P>
	April 10: Actor Max von Sydow is 70. Actor Omar Sharif is 67.  
Reggae artist Bunny Wailer is 52. Actor Steven Seagal is 48. Singer 
Terre Roche of The Roches is 46. Actor Peter MacNicol is 45. 
Musician Steven Gustafson of 10,000 Maniacs is 42. Singer-producer 
Kenneth ``Babyface'' Edmonds is 41. Musician Brian Setzer is 40. 
Rapper Afrika Bambaataa is 39. Singer Kenny Lattimore is 29. 
</P>
