<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Down; Gold Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar was down against most other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold was mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0749, up from $1.0745 Tuesday. The  
British pound was quoted at $1.6125, down from $1.6126. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar was at 118.66 Japanese yen, down from 120.44.  
</P>
<P>
	In New York, the euro was at $1.0816 and the British pound was  
at $1.6156. The dollar was quoted at 118.43 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Tuesday: 1.4845 Swiss  
francs, down from 1.4854; and 1.5085 Canadian dollars, down from 
1.5130. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8195 German marks, down from 1.8202; 
6.1025 French francs, down from 6.1048; 2.0502 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0509; and 1,801.35 Italian lire, down from 1,802.02. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $279.70 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$279.40 on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $279.50, up from $279.30.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell 30 cents in Hong Kong to close at $279.95.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.04 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$5.02. 
</P>
</TEXT>
