<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Down Against Top Currencie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The dollar fell against the yen and other major  
currencies Wednesday after a rally in Asian trading fizzled. 
</P>
<P>
	Dealers had expected the dollar to rise against the yen as  
investors adjusted their positions on the last day of the Japanese 
fiscal year Wednesday. But the currency reversed course, falling 
against the yen and euro. 
</P>
<P>
	In late New York trading, the euro was quoted at $1.0768, up  
from $1.0715 late Tuesday. The dollar also was quoted at 118.97 
Japanese yen, down from 120.36 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar also was quoted at 1.4827 Swiss francs, down from  
1.4899, and 1.5095 Canadian dollars, down from 1.5117. The British 
pound rose to $1.6116 from $1.6108. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed rate. 
Based on Wednesday's euro rate, the dollar was worth: 1.8162 German 
marks, down from 1.8255; 6.0901 French francs, down from 6.1237; 
and 1,798.56 Italian lire, down from 1,808.32. 
</P>
</TEXT>
