<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wizards' Meola To Miss Six Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Kansas City Wizards goalkeeper Tony  
Meola will be sidelined for six months after undergoing 
arthroscopic knee surgery, the team announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Meola suffered a complete ACL tear March 17 when he turned and  
planted to kick a ball during practice. 
</P>
<P>
	Chris Snitko, who missed the first two games of the season with  
an injured back, will replace Meola. 
