<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Sunny skies and unseasonably warm weather prevailed over much of  
the East on Wednesday, while light rain fell in the Tennessee 
Valley and along parts of the West Coast. 
</P>
<P>
	High temperatures warmed the Great Lakes, Ohio Valley, Northeast  
and Mid-Atlantic states. The thermometer rose to the 60s and 70s as 
far north as Michigan. Temperatures were just as high across most 
of Nebraska, Iowa and Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	Light rain fell over spots in Kentucky and Tennessee, east to  
the southern Appalachians and into Georgia and Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	Skies are mostly cloudy across the lower-Mississippi Valley, and  
were clear over western Kansas and the Oklahoma and Texas 
panhandles. 
</P>
<P>
	Scattered showers doused the West Coast, Great Basin and Pacific  
Northwest. Snow fell in the higher elevations of Utah. 
</P>
<P>
	Fair and dry weather prevailed across the central and southern  
Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
	In northern Arizona, high winds blew over trucks on Interstate  
40 near Flagstaff, killing one person. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from an afternoon high  
of 84 in Punta Gorda, Fla., to a low of 9 in Stanley, Idaho. 
</P>
</TEXT>
