<HEADLINE> Entertainment Highlights in History  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Entertainment highlights during the week of April 4-10:  
</P>
<P>
	50 years ago: Kirk Douglas starred in ``Champion,'' with Arthur  
Kennedy and Marilyn Maxwell. 
</P>
<P>
	40 years ago: The Academy Awards show ran short, and with 20  
minutes of air time to fill, comedian Jerry Lewis suggested showing 
``Three Stooges'' shorts. Lewis was kidding. 
</P>
<P>
	35 years ago: The Beatles held the top five positions on  
Billboard's Top 100 chart. ``Can't Buy Me Love'' was No. 1, 
followed by ``Twist and Shout,'' ``She Loves You,'' ``I Want to 
Hold Your Hand'' and ``Please Please Me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	25 years ago: Gene Hackman starred in Frances Ford Coppola's  
``The Conversation.'' 
</P>
<P>
	20 years ago: ``The Deer Hunter'' won five Oscars, including  
best picture and best director. 
</P>
<P>
	15 years ago: ``Terms of Endearment'' won five Oscars, including  
best picture and best director. 
</P>
<P>
	And a record 40 British acts appeared on the U.S. Top 100 chart.  
</P>
<P>
	10 years ago: The country-rock band Alabama was named artist of  
the decade by the Academy of Country Music. 
</P>
<P>
	And Pepsi Cola dropped plans to run more ads featuring Madonna  
and her single ``Like a Prayer'' because of complaints and boycott 
threats about the religious imagery in a video for the song. Pepsi 
had no connection with the video. But consumers had confused the 
song and video and had complained to the company. 
</P>
<P>
	Five years ago: Charles Kuralt hosted his last episode of  
``Sunday Morning'' on CBS. Charles Osgood replaced him. 
</P>
<P>
	One year ago: Bob Keeshan, best known as Captain Kangaroo, was  
inducted into the National Association of Broadcasters' Hall of 
Fame. 

</P>
<P>
	Spoken 10 years ago:  
</P>
<P>
	``I don't view myself as successful. I think of myself as  
lucky.'' -- Actor Tom Hanks. 

</P>
<P>
	Spoken five years ago:  
</P>
<P>
	``You either have it or you don't. I'm in the best possible  
position I can be in, because I have talent, a commodity I can 
sell, that I can ram down people's throats.'' -- Actress Jodie 
Foster. 

</P>
<P>
	Spoken one year ago:  
</P>
<P>
	``I'm kind of a mediocre guitar player. But sometimes the  
earnestness of a so-so guitar player doing their best sounds better 
than a fantastic guitar player being sloppy.'' -- Singer Amy Grant. 
</P>
