<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Cuts Key Interest Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Canada's central bank lowered its key interest  
rate by a quarter percentage point today, to 5 percent, citing low 
inflation in Canada and calmer financial markets. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bank of Canada's rate cut had been widely anticipated since  
the country's main inflation rate dipped below the central bank's 1 
percent to 3 percent target band in February. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the fourth cut in the bank rate, the interest the Bank of  
Canada charges on overnight loans to commercial banks, in the last 
seven months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
